y fought battle mobile bay during civil war grace was very curious child lifelong trait at age seven she decided determine how alarm clock worked dismantled seven alarm clocks before her mother realized what she was doing she was then limited one clock for her preparatory school education she attended hartridge school plainfield new jersey rejected for early admission vassar college at age her test scores latin were too low she was admitted following year she graduated phi beta kappa from vassar with bachelor's degree mathematics physics earned her master's degree at yale university she earned phd mathematics from yale under direction øystein ore her dissertation new types irreducibility criteria was published that same year hopper began teaching mathematics at vassar was promoted associate professor she was married new york university professor vincent foster hopper 1906–76 from until their divorce she did not marry again but she kept his surname career world war ii hopper's signatures on duty officer signup sheet for bureau ships computation project at harvard which built operated mark i during world war ii hopper obtained leave absence from vassar was sworn into united states navy reserve one many women volunteer serve waves she had get exemption enlist she was pounds kg below navy minimum weight pounds kg she reported december trained at naval reserve midshipmen's school at smith college northampton massachusetts hopper graduated first her class was assigned bureau ships computation project at harvard university lieutenant junior grade she served on mark i computer programming staff headed by howard h aiken hopper aiken coauthored three papers on mark i also known automatic sequence controlled calculator hopper's request transfer regular navy at end war was declined due her age she continued serve navy reserve hopper remained at harvard computation lab until turning down full professorship at vassar favor working research fellow under navy contract at harvard un