eceived standing ovation at conclusion her remarks she often recounted that during her service she was frequently asked by admirals generals why satellite communication would take so long so during many her lectures she illustrated nanosecond using salvaged obsolete bell system pair telephone cable cut inch cm lengths distance that light travels one nanosecond handed out individual wires her listeners although no longer serving officer she always wore her navy full dress uniform these lectures which allowed by us navy uniform regulations most important thing i've accomplished other than building compiler training young people they come me you know say 'do you think we can do this' i say try i back 'em up they need that i keep track them they get older i stir 'em up at intervals so they don't forget take chances she was interred with full military honors arlington national cemetery continuing honor her service accomplishments us naval academy announced on september that will name its future cyber building after her awards hopper was awarded inaugural data processing management association man year award now called distinguished information sciences award annual grace murray hopper award for outstanding young computer professionals was established by association for computing machinery first american first woman any nationality be made distinguished fellow british computer society american association university women achievement award honorary doctor science from marquette university honorary doctor letters from western new england college now western new england university upon her retirement she received defense distinguished service medal first computer history museum fellow award recipient for contributions development programming languages for standardization efforts for lifelong naval service golden gavel award at toastmasters international convention washington dc national medal technology elected fellow american academy arts sciences uss hopper ddg-70 was lau